The <strong><code>outline</code></strong> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS">CSS</a> property is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Shorthand_properties">shorthand</a> to set various outline properties in a single declaration: <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/outline-style" title="The outline-style CSS property sets the style of an element's outline. An outline is a line that is drawn around an element, outside the border."><code>outline-style</code></a>, <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/outline-width" title="The outline-width CSS property sets the thickness of an element's outline. An outline is a line that is drawn around an element, outside the border."><code>outline-width</code></a>, and <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/outline-color" title="The outline-color CSS property sets the color of an element's outline."><code>outline-color</code></a>.